benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/block - Block a bundle

covered: POST method: Valid payload scenarios covered (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04)
Missing/invalid bundleId handling covered (TC06, TC07, TC05)
Large payloads and edge inputs (TC16, TC19, TC20)
Error handling and service unavailability (TC17, TC28, TC30)
Regression scenarios for special characters and backward compatibility (TC23, TC24)
gaps: Duplicate submission handling (idempotency) not explicitly tested
Internal server error (500) explicit coverage not present (only 503/502, partial) or DB failure scenarios beyond 400/503
Explicit 401 vs 400 distinction for missing required headers could be clarified (covered by TC09 but nuance not separated)
Missing explicit test for 405/405-like method not allowed scenarios
No explicit test focusing on server-side validation messages for every invalid field beyond generic 400
No test focusing on partial updates or optional field behavior specific to API version compatibility beyond TC24
recommendations: Add a test for duplicate submissions to verify idempotency and proper handling of repeated requests.
Add tests around caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) to confirm caching behavior where applicable.
Introduce rate-limiting tests to ensure proper handling of rapid consecutive requests.
Add explicit 500 Internal Server Error scenarios (e.g., simulated DB failure) to validate server error handling beyond 503/502.
Clarify and optionally split header validation edge cases (e.g., missing vs invalid Authorization) with dedicated scenarios to ensure clear error codes.
Add a targeted test for 405 Method Not Allowed if the API could be invoked with unsupported methods on this path.
